en: Staff at their desks, 223rd Co. C.C.C., TVA P-10, Powell Station, Tennessee

This photograph shows five members of the Civilian Conservation Corps headquarters personnel of the 223rd Company, TVA P-10, in Powell Station, Tennessee. The room has wooden desks, a typewriter, file cabinets, file boxes, a coal-burning stove. In the back of the room, there is an organizational chart for the company that shows a division of five work crews and other personnel. donor: Haslbauer, Otto F. Photo reads Spencer and Wyckoff, Detroit
